This article is a transcript of a speech given by President Joe Biden on the South Lawn. He thanks the families of members of Congress for their support and acknowledges the pressure they face. He also thanks Speaker Nancy Pelosi and other political leaders. Biden mentions a favorite picture of his children at a congressional picnic and emphasizes the importance of friendship and working together. Vice President Kamala Harris also speaks, thanking the families for their sacrifices and their contribution to the country. The article concludes with Biden urging everyone to get going and saying, "God bless America."